ABUJA – Peter Obi has resigned from the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Obi, a former Anambra State governor, was until his resignation one of the 15 aspirants vying for the presidential ticket of the PDP. The letter conveying his resignation from the party, which was dated Tuesday, May 24, was submitted to the National Chairman of the PDP, Dr. Iyorchia Ayu, on Wednesday, May 25. Sources say he may pitch his tent with the Social Democratic Party (SDP). Below is the letter to Dr. Ayu Abuja - Former Vice-President of Nigeria, Atiku Abubakar, is planning to retain Peter Obi as his running mate if he clinches the presidential ticket of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), sources have said. The duo clinched the PDP presidential ticket in the 2019 general elections although they lost to the… In "Top Stories" Peter Obi (left) and Doyin Okupe ABUJA - Barely one to the conduct of the presidential primaries of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), supporters of a leading aspirant, Peter Obi, have raised the alarm over plans to force him to step down. Doing Okupe, one of Obi’s top campaign managers,… In "Top Stories" A former Ekiti State Governor, Ayodele Fayose is no longer a member of the Peoples Democratic Party’s zoning committee He resigned over his presidential ambition. Fayose made this known in a letter dated April 5, 2022, and addressed to the Chairman of the PDP zoning committee and Benue State Governor,… In "Politics"